The paper discusses anomaly detection in cloud computing using machine learning theory, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). It also mentions the use of extreme learning machine (ELM), which is a type of neural network and falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the challenges faced in the cloud computing platform, such as imbalance dataset, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of the discriminative model, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the ranking of anomalies, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
